               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18401019-name-1020" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18401019-name-1020" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18401019-name-1020" type="surname" value="CORNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18401019-name-1020" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE CORNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am assistant to Mr. Thomas Vesper, a pawnbroker, in Sydney-place, Commercial-road. On the 21st of October I was behind the counter, and heard a cry of "Stop thief"—I went out at the side door, which opens into Exmouth-street, and saw the prisoner running away as fast as he could—I stopped him with the assistance of another man in the street—he inquired for his basket—I said I had not seen it—he asked me to look after it—I inquired, and could not find it—as I was bringing him along I saw Jesse M'Pheraon—she pointed to the curb, where I found this coat, close to the shop door.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
